SHORTCUTS:-

        run                   = alt + r

        open/close explorer   = alt + 1
        close panel tab       = ctrl + j

        format code           = alt + f
        word wrap             = alt + w

        close tabs            = ctrl + f4
        rename                = f2

float a = 4;   //no error since 4 is a integer and integer can be stored in float
float a=4.0;   //error...as 4.0 is double and double cannot be stored in float

float x = 5.3f;
x+=0.3; No error   //ShortHand Operator does Implicit Conversion
x = x + 0.3 ; Error :- Cannot store double in float

byte x = 3;
x+=2;   //No error bcoz implicit conversion or value just incremented by 2
x=x+2;  //Error 2 is a integer which means type mismatch storing int in byte not possibke

--int/int will always yields int (even if you store it in double)
if you want ans in point then make any of a or b ine expression a/b as float/double

NOTE:-
        int a=4,b=3;
        double c=a/b;
        System.out.println(c);   // O/P=1.0

        double a=4,b=3;
        double c=a/b;
        System.out.println(c);   // O/P=1.33..

        double x=4;
        System.out.println(x);   //O/P=4.0



long x = 999_999_999_999_999;

{dividend = divisor * Quotient + Remainder}

a%b --> (0,b-1)
Eg:- something%3 = 0,1,2    [let something = 3,4,5,6,7 ...now check]

if Nr<Dr then Nr%Dr=Nr always   [1%10=1] (since 1=10*0+1)  [3%5=3] (since 3=5*0+3)

PascalCase - for naming Classes  [Scanner , Arrays.toString()]
camelCase - for naming Variables and Methods  [nextInt(),println(),toString(),]

for packages - small or camelCase

Primitive datatypes: Built in / Predefined + size and range fixed

